<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1523,1886]" pageId="19" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,335,1523,1549]" pageId="19" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Frons as broad as high, fastigium triangular, not sulcate, not surpassing the margins of antennal sockets, with two basal tubercles. Scapus of antennae with terminal spine. Pronotum granulated. Flight organs well developed with hyaline alae. Prosternum with two spines. Femoral spines of the same coloration as the legs, but with black tips. Forefemora at least as long as the pronotum. Only the genicular lobes of middle femora unarmed, all others with terminal spine. 
<collectingCountry box="[908,967,1673,1699]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="60">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibiae dorsally with inner spines almost two times longer than the external ones. Supra-anal plate subtriangular, almost twice as long as broad. Cerci strongly modified (
<figureCitation box="[376,448,1748,1774]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="20.[151,255,901,925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,213,879]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,195,880]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pizatettix sanctaecrucis (Piza, 1973) comb. nov. male subgenital plate and cerci A. ventral view, B. ventrolateral view C. lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198413/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="60">
Fig. 
<number box="[431,448,1748,1774]" pageId="19" pageNumber="60" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), of the same length as or longer than the subgenital plate including styli. Styli long, a little shorter than the subgenital plate, basally fused, and apparently fused with the subgenital plate as well, both structures differentiated by a slight offset of the latter, where the styli originate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1523,1886]" box="[198,1187,1860,1886]" pageId="19" pageNumber="60">
